1
00:00:00,140 --> 00:00:05,210
In this video we are going to learn challenges of asynchronous communication.

2
00:00:05,240 --> 00:00:09,860
The first challenges is single point of failure message brokers.

3
00:00:10,430 --> 00:00:17,000
The message broker becomes a single point of failure if we don't configure the message broker properly.

4
00:00:17,060 --> 00:00:20,090
It can become a problem for our architecture.

5
00:00:20,660 --> 00:00:25,670
We shouldn't rely on all communication with a single node of the message brokers.

6
00:00:25,670 --> 00:00:33,620
Instead, we should scale it and use hybrid communication with synchronous and asynchronous in our cases.

7
00:00:35,220 --> 00:00:37,500
And second challenges is debugging.

8
00:00:37,530 --> 00:00:44,280
It is often difficult to debug issues with asynchronous communication, because it can be hard to trace

9
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:47,940
the flow of the single operation across service boundaries.

10
00:00:48,060 --> 00:00:55,560
Since there is no clear data flow now and messages get processed when they arrive to consumer systems,

11
00:00:55,560 --> 00:01:01,800
debugging of the flow and the payload of the events takes so many times and hard to debug at the same

12
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:02,430
time.

13
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:09,570
So this is why it is usually a good idea to generate a unique ID when the message is received, so that

14
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:12,840
you can track with the unique ID into the logs.

15
00:01:12,870 --> 00:01:15,450
Also, we can call this correlation ID.

16
00:01:15,750 --> 00:01:22,620
And another challenges is at least once delivery and not guarantee an order of messages.

17
00:01:23,310 --> 00:01:29,250
Message broker systems are a very good fit for event driven microservice communication, but mostly

18
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:33,630
they use at least once delivery and not guarantee order of messages.

19
00:01:33,630 --> 00:01:40,980
So we should embrace these message delivery mechanism with applying idempotency consumers and not designing

20
00:01:40,980 --> 00:01:42,420
Fifo requires cases.

